            "body": "@davidism ok, we can avoid adding extra messages, but what do you think of changing the current one to `* Serving Flask app (The module \"app.py\" will be lazily loaded)` as it is explicit.\r\n\r\nI know the usual way is seeing errors in the debugger, but this is not an application error this is a load error, the same way `shell` and `routes` command shows explicit error in the command line and also errors are shown in command line when `lazy loader` is False.\r\n\r\nI can imagine a scenario where developer is counting on the stdout messages to assert some functional test."
